# SEC EDGAR fair-access requires a descriptive User-Agent (your name + email).
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values. Never commit a real .env.
SEC_EDGAR_USER_AGENT=Your Name your@email.com

# Shared secret gating POST /api/extract (the slow, EDGAR-fetching endpoint). REQUIRED
# before exposing the app over a public tunnel: without it that path fails closed (503).
# Share the value with reviewers out-of-band; the frontend prompts for it and stores it in
# localStorage. /health, /api/demo, /api/eval and the static SPA stay open.
# Generate: python -c "import secrets; print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"
SEC10K_ACCESS_TOKEN=replace_with_a_long_random_secret

# --- Cloudflare tunnel (OPTIONAL) ---
# `docker compose up` runs a QUICK tunnel by default: no account, no token, ephemeral
# https://<random>.trycloudflare.com URL (`docker compose logs cloudflared`). Set this ONLY
# for a stable NAMED tunnel (and swap the cloudflared command in docker-compose.yml). It is a
# Cloudflare-ISSUED connector token, not a string you generate. Leave unset for the quick tunnel.
# CLOUDFLARE_TUNNEL_TOKEN=cloudflare_issued_named_tunnel_token

# --- LLM escalation tier (REAL, via the GitHub Copilot SDK; graceful-fallback) ---
# Set GH_TOKEN to enable the REAL escalation tier: low-confidence boundaries are adjudicated by a
# Copilot model (sec10k/copilot_client.py, "index-don't-generate" line-ref only). The SDK auto-
# reads GH_TOKEN / COPILOT_GITHUB_TOKEN / GITHUB_TOKEN; on the HOST run `gh auth token` (a PAT with
# the Copilot Requests permission) and paste it here -- no interactive login in the container.
# On the deployed app the tier is controlled PER REQUEST by the web UI toggle (default OFF); a real
# call still requires a token here. SEC10K_LLM_ESCALATION is now only the DEFAULT for CLI/library
# callers that don't pass an explicit flag -- the UI toggle overrides it. We measured the tier and it
# gave no independent-signal gain on our gold (research/llm-measurement-findings.md), so the
# deterministic path is the $0 default. LEAVE these unset for the graceful $0 fallback (offline suite
# stays network-free). Optional dep: ".[llm]".
# GH_TOKEN=paste_output_of_gh_auth_token
# SEC10K_LLM_ESCALATION=1
#
# Default escalation model is claude-opus-4.8 (sec10k/llm_models.py). The web UI lets you pick per
# request (GET /api/models lists the live options); COPILOT_MODEL overrides the server-side default.
# COPILOT_MODEL=claude-opus-4.8
